ption>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 23:25:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/%f0%9f%9a%a8-you-are-already-dead-and-dont-know-it</guid></item><item><title>阻断基于 GDF15 的大脑能量感应的潜在风险</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/potential-risks-of-blocking-gdf15%e2%80%90based-brain-energy-sensing</link><description>GDF15 向大脑发出能量压力信号，当身体保存和重新分配能量时，会导致令人不快的症状。在虚弱和癌症等情况下，抑制 GDF15 信号传导有望改善症状，但可能会以长期健康和生存为代价。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/potential-risks-of-blocking-gdf15e28090based-brain-energy-sensing3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 23:10:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/potential-risks-of-blocking-gdf15%e2%80%90based-brain-energy-sensing</guid></item><item><title>MRAP2 通过被肥胖相关遗传变异破坏的保守机制增强 GPCR 信号传导</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/mrap2-potentiates-gpcr-signaling-by-conserved-mechanisms-that-are-disrupted-by-obesity-associated-genetic-variants</link><description>贾马鲁丁等人。研究了 MRAP2 辅助蛋白如何通过三种食欲调节 GPCR 增强信号传导。 MRAP2 破坏 GPCR 寡聚化以形成相互作用，其细胞质区域对于信号传导至关重要。 MRAP2 变体调节受体组成活性、增强内化并减少信号传导，从而导致人类体重增加和高血糖。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mrap2-potentiates-gpcr-signaling-by-conserved-mechanisms-that-are-disrupted-by-obesity-associated-genetic-variants2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 22:55:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/mrap2-potentiates-gpcr-signaling-by-conserved-mechanisms-that-are-disrupted-by-obesity-associated-genetic-variants</guid></item></channel></rss>